{"session_id":"e88a43b1-b93b-4528-9303-047573b95257","user_input":{"occasion_freetext":"I have to say goodbye to a brilliant colleague at work.","answers":[{"question":"What is your colleague’s name, and where are they headed or why are they leaving (if appropriate to mention)?","answer":"eric, retirement"},{"question":"Are there one or two shared accomplishments, quirks, or stories you’d like included?","answer":"no"},{"question":"What was your very first impression of Eric, and what specific moment—where he was, what he did or said—made you realize that first impression was wrong or incomplete?","answer":"just give me a generic speech"},{"question":"Even one tiny detail will make this feel personal: what is a habit Eric has at work that everyone recognizes—an exact phrase he says, a mug or desk object, a routine, or the way he handles a problem?","answer":"he eats salads everyday"},{"question":"Eric’s daily salads are a good start—can you give me one concrete detail: what does he call them, where does he eat them, or has anyone ever counted how many days in a row he brought one?","answer":"everyday, the same salad, same sauce"},{"question":"What exactly was in Eric’s same daily salad—and what was the sauce? If you can picture it, tell me the container or bowl he carried it in and where he ate it.","answer":"lettuce with mayonaise"},{"question":"For one sincere line beyond the salad: what is one specific thing Eric was exceptionally good at—solving a certain problem, helping people, knowing a system—and can you name a real example or project where colleagues relied on him?","answer":"he is good at everything, huge loss for the company"},{"question":"For a final specific detail: can you name one ordinary work moment when Eric’s “good at everything” showed—what had gone wrong, what did he do, and what did someone say afterward? Even a small example is enough.","answer":"technical, leadership"}]},"occasion_profile":{"occasion_type":"farewell","sensitive_mode":false,"speaker_role":"colleague","honoree":"a departing colleague","audience_composition":["coworkers","workplace leadership"],"formality":"semi_formal","target_length_seconds":120,"humor_ceiling":"playful","sentiment_ratio":0.6,"off_limits":["the colleague's reasons for leaving unless they have made them public","layoffs or workplace conflict","personal or confidential details"],"cultural_notes":null},"material":{"stories":[{"story":"Eric is retiring after being known in the workplace for bringing and eating the exact same salad every day: lettuce with mayonnaise.","comedy_potential":5,"sentiment_potential":2},{"story":"Eric is described as exceptionally capable across both technical work and leadership, and as a significant loss to the company when he retires.","comedy_potential":1,"sentiment_potential":7}]},"skeleton":{"premise":"Eric’s retirement marks the departure of someone whose remarkable consistency—whether in a daily salad or in technical and leadership excellence—made the whole workplace stronger.","beats":[{"beat":1,"type":"opener","target_words":40,"purpose":"Welcome everyone and immediately establish Eric’s recognizable daily-salad legacy.","content":["Open by saying that retirement speeches usually try to capture a person in one memorable image.","Name Eric’s image: the exact same daily salad—lettuce with mayonnaise, every day."],"joke":{"mechanism":"misdirection","story_source":"Eric brought and ate the same lettuce-with-mayonnaise salad every day","setup":"Frame the salad as evidence of a man with an unusually precise long-term strategy.","callback_plant":"Plant the idea that Eric’s consistency was never accidental."}},{"beat":2,"type":"humorous_story_beat","target_words":45,"purpose":"Escalate the salad observation from a workplace quirk into a light portrait of Eric’s dependable style.","content":["Describe the dependable repetition: same salad, same sauce, every day.","Gently contrast the simplicity of lunch with the breadth of Eric’s professional capability.","Avoid guessing at ingredients, containers, locations, or coworkers’ reactions."],"joke":{"mechanism":"rule of three","story_source":"Eric’s daily identical salad and his technical/leadership capability","setup":"List the predictable elements of the lunch routine, then contrast them with Eric’s ability to handle whatever work brought his way.","callback_plant":"Connect the salad’s reliability to Eric’s reliability at work."}},{"beat":3,"type":"pivot","target_words":35,"purpose":"Turn from affectionate humor to the significance of Eric’s retirement.","content":["State that the salad is an easy detail to remember, but it is not the reason Eric will be missed.","Name the real loss: Eric’s rare combination of technical strength and leadership.","Shift delivery from playful to direct and appreciative."],"joke":null},{"beat":4,"type":"sincere_payoff","target_words":80,"purpose":"Pay off the premise by honoring Eric’s broad professional impact and the gap his retirement creates.","content":["Say that Eric was someone colleagues could rely on across both technical work and leadership.","Emphasize that being good at everything is more than skill: it gives others confidence, direction, and support.","Acknowledge plainly that his retirement is a huge loss for the company.","Thank Eric for the standard he set and for what he contributed to colleagues and the workplace."],"emotional_core":"Eric’s consistency reflected a deeper dependability: he was exceptionally capable in both technical work and leadership, and his absence will be deeply felt.","gap_for_punch_up_writer":"If available, add one verified example of a technical problem Eric solved or a leadership moment that shows how colleagues relied on him."},{"beat":5,"type":"closer_toast","target_words":45,"purpose":"End warmly, lightly, and memorably by returning to the opening image.","content":["Wish Eric a happy, well-earned retirement.","Return to the idea that Eric brought consistency, capability, and calm to work every day.","Invite the room to raise a glass to Eric."],"joke":{"mechanism":"callback","story_source":"Eric’s same daily lettuce-and-mayonnaise salad","payoff":"Lightly wish Eric a retirement full of choices—while respectfully allowing that the same salad may remain one of them."}}]},"draft":{"version":2,"beats":[{"beat":1,"type":"opener","text":"Retirement speeches try to capture someone in one memorable image. For Eric, that image is clear: the same salad, every day. Lettuce with mayonnaise. It was a small sign of something we all came to count on—Eric knew what worked, and he showed up with it.","delivery_note":"Pause two beats before “Lettuce with mayonnaise.”"},{"beat":2,"type":"humorous_story_beat","text":"Same salad. Same sauce. Every day. And when a technical question came up or a team needed direction, Eric was someone people looked to. His lunch was predictable. His ability to be useful, steady, and prepared was too."},{"beat":3,"type":"pivot","text":"The salad is an easy thing to remember, but it isn’t why Eric will be missed. He’ll be missed because, whether the work needed technical know-how or a clear hand to guide it, Eric gave people confidence that they could move forward."},{"beat":4,"type":"sincere_payoff","text":"That is a rare kind of colleague. Eric did not just bring technical capability; he was someone colleagues could turn to when they needed direction. He made difficult work feel more manageable and helped people feel supported in the process. That combination of knowledge, calm, and leadership has mattered throughout this workplace. Eric, your retirement is a huge loss for this company. Thank you for the reliability you brought, the example you set, and the difference you made for the people who worked alongside you.","delivery_note":"Slow down for the final three sentences."},{"beat":5,"type":"closer_toast","text":"Eric, we wish you a happy, healthy, and very well-earned retirement. Thank you for the capability, steadiness, and generosity you brought here every day. Please raise a glass to Eric—and to all the good things ahead.","delivery_note":"Pause before inviting the toast."}]},"audience_feedback":{"personas":[{"name":"Maya, longtime teammate","role":"coworker","tastes":"Enjoys affectionate workplace specifics and gentle teasing, as long as the honoree is clearly respected."},{"name":"Daniel, newer colleague","role":"coworker","tastes":"Needs clear context and concrete examples; less responsive to broad claims about someone he may not know well."},{"name":"Priya, department leader","role":"workplace leadership","tastes":"Prefers polished, dignified recognition that balances warmth with a credible account of professional impact."},{"name":"Tom, pragmatic senior manager","role":"workplace leadership","tastes":"Values concise remarks and has little patience for generic corporate praise or jokes that overstay their welcome."}],"beat_feedback":[{"beat":1,"reactions":[{"persona":"Maya, longtime teammate","reaction":"smile","comment":"“That salad is a recognizably Eric detail, and tying it to dependability makes the teasing feel affectionate.”"},{"persona":"Daniel, newer colleague","reaction":"smile","comment":"“I immediately understand the detail and why it represents his consistency.”"},{"persona":"Priya, department leader","reaction":"smile","comment":"“The opening uses the lunch detail briefly, then gives it a respectful meaning rather than turning it into a roast.”"},{"persona":"Tom, pragmatic senior manager","reaction":"flat","comment":"“It is clear and compact, but ‘knew what worked’ is a fairly expected conclusion from the routine.”"}],"criteria":{"specificity":"Pass: “the same salad,” lettuce, and mayonnaise are concrete details.","surprise":"Needs work: the connection between a repeated lunch and reliability is natural but predictable.","clarity":"Pass: listeners need no prior context to follow the image.","safety":"Pass: the detail is presented warmly and does not dwell on embarrassment.","economy":"Pass: the setup is concise and establishes the central image quickly."}},{"beat":2,"reactions":[{"persona":"Maya, longtime teammate","reaction":"smile","comment":"“The simple contrast between a predictable lunch and a dependable colleague lands nicely.”"},{"persona":"Daniel, newer colleague","reaction":"flat","comment":"“I understand that Eric was helpful, but I still do not have a picture of what he actually did.”"},{"persona":"Priya, department leader","reaction":"smile","comment":"“This moves smoothly from the personal quirk to his technical and leadership value.”"},{"persona":"Tom, pragmatic senior manager","reaction":"flat","comment":"“‘Useful, steady, and prepared’ is agreeable, but it could describe almost any strong employee.”"}],"criteria":{"specificity":"Needs work: the salad remains specific, but the account of Eric’s work is abstract.","surprise":"Pass: the lunch-to-work contrast is modest but clean.","clarity":"Pass: the intended point about dependability is easy to follow.","safety":"Pass: the humor remains light and respectful.","economy":"Pass: no sentence feels unnecessary."}},{"beat":3,"reactions":[{"persona":"Maya, longtime teammate","reaction":"smile","comment":"“It makes a graceful turn from the joke to why Eric truly matters to the team.”"},{"persona":"Daniel, newer colleague","reaction":"flat","comment":"“‘Technical know-how’ and ‘a clear hand’ sound good, but I would remember this more with one real example.”"},{"persona":"Priya, department leader","reaction":"smile","comment":"“The pivot is direct, appropriately appreciative, and well suited to a semi-formal retirement farewell.”"},{"persona":"Tom, pragmatic senior manager","reaction":"flat","comment":"“This is efficient, but it leans on familiar leadership language rather than a distinct observation.”"}],"criteria":{"specificity":"Needs work: technical expertise and guidance are broad labels without an observable example.","surprise":"Pass: the tonal transition is expected and effective for this kind of speech.","clarity":"Pass: the reason Eric will be missed is clearly stated.","safety":"Pass: fully respectful and within workplace boundaries.","economy":"Pass: it does its transition job without lingering."}},{"beat":4,"reactions":[{"persona":"Maya, longtime teammate","reaction":"moved","comment":"“The thought that he made difficult work manageable and people feel supported is genuinely warm.”"},{"persona":"Daniel, newer colleague","reaction":"flat","comment":"“The praise is sincere, but I still cannot picture a moment when Eric gave that support.”"},{"persona":"Priya, department leader","reaction":"smile","comment":"“It credibly recognizes both his technical contribution and his leadership, while keeping the focus on colleagues.”"},{"persona":"Tom, pragmatic senior manager","reaction":"flat","comment":"“The message is sound, but ‘knowledge, calm, and leadership’ and ‘the example you set’ are polished generalities.”"}],"criteria":{"specificity":"Needs work: this central tribute relies on abstract traits rather than a concrete behavior or example.","surprise":"Pass: sincere recognition does not require a punchline.","clarity":"Pass: Eric’s professional value and the scale of the loss are unmistakable.","safety":"Pass: warm, professional, and not overclaiming any confidential details.","economy":"Needs work: several sentences restate his capability, support, and leadership in closely related terms."}},{"beat":5,"reactions":[{"persona":"Maya, longtime teammate","reaction":"smile","comment":"“It is warm, straightforward, and ends where a toast should: with good wishes for Eric.”"},{"persona":"Daniel, newer colleague","reaction":"smile","comment":"“The gratitude and invitation to raise a glass are easy to follow and give the speech a clear finish.”"},{"persona":"Priya, department leader","reaction":"smile","comment":"“This is a dignified closing that keeps the final emphasis on Eric rather than the lunch joke.”"},{"persona":"Tom, pragmatic senior manager","reaction":"smile","comment":"“It is brief, professional, and does not force a callback that could undercut the tribute.”"}],"criteria":{"specificity":"Needs work: the language is warm but largely general, aside from the established idea of daily steadiness.","surprise":"Pass: a clean toast need not be surprising.","clarity":"Pass: the retirement wish and toast invitation are unmistakable.","safety":"Pass: the close is respectful and avoids returning to potentially overused food humor.","economy":"Pass: concise and appropriately final."}}],"verdict":"pass","revision_targets":[]},"final":{"title":"","speech_text":"","estimated_duration_seconds":0,"delivery_tips":[]},"loop":{"iteration":2,"max_iterations":3,"stop_reason":"audience_pass"}}
